As noted by @ksdboasit in https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues/1058, the new project name validation code does not seem to apply to WebStorm.

> I tried the same in WebStorm (2017.1.3), and here there was no initial validation. It just failed to create the project when using an upper case letter.

@alexander-doroshko : we're using `io.flutter.module.FlutterModuleBuilder#validateModuleName` here; is there a better approach?  How do you recommend validating names for WebStorm project creation?
